\sum_{y=1}^x(1-\theta)^{y-1}\theta=\sum_{n=0}^{x-1}(1-\theta)^n\theta=\theta\sum_{n=0}^{x-1}(1-\theta)^n=\theta\frac{(1-\theta)^x-1}{(1-\theta)-1}=1-(1-\theta)^x.
\begin{align*} \sum_{y=1}^x (1-\theta)^{y-1}\theta  =& (1-\theta)^{1-1}\theta + (1-\theta)^{2-1}\theta+(1-\theta)^{3-1}\theta + \cdots + (1-\theta)^{x-1}\theta\\  =& (1-\theta)^0\theta + (1-\theta)^1\theta+(1-\theta)^2\theta + \cdots + (1-\theta)^{x-1}\theta\\  =& \sum_{z=0}^{x-1} (1-\theta)^z\theta \end{align*}
